public class PrivateMethodExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Person p = new Person();
        
       
        
        p.show(); 
    }
}
class Person {
    
    private void displaySecret() {
        System.out.println("This is a private message. Only Person class can access it.");
    }

    
    public void show() {
        System.out.println("Public method is accessible everywhere.");
        displaySecret();
    }
}

public class PrivateMethodExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Person p = new Person();
        
       
        
        p.show(); 
    }
}
output
Public method is accessible everywhere.
This is a private message. Only Person class can access it.
